						               													<description>This is another in the &amp;quot;Bite-Size&amp;quot; range of Trivial Pursuit games. Trivial Pursuit: Genus Edition &amp;ndash; Bite Size is intended as a portable travel game. The game is packaged in a wedge (&amp;quot;piece-of-pie&amp;quot;) shaped box.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game does not feature a game board, and thus, there is no roll-and-move mechanic. Instead, players roll the colour coded die, and answers a question matching the colour rolled. The colours correspond to categories that include geography, entertainment, history, arts &amp;amp; literature, science &amp;amp; nature, and sports &amp;amp; leisure. If a player correctly answers a question, he may &amp;quot;go for a wedge&amp;quot; by answering another question in the same category. If he does so, he keeps that card. If the player answers a question incorrectly, it is the next players turn. Play ends when a player has collected six cards/correctly answered 12 questions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
